SIMPLE: idealization
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Idealization
<hw>I*de`al*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act or process of idealizing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>The representation of natural
objects, scenes, etc., in such a way as to show their most important
characteristics; the study of the ideal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A defense mechanism that splits something one is
ambivalent about into two representations -- one good and one bad.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>something that exists only as an idea.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>a portrayal of something as ideal.</def>
<wns>[wns=3]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> glorification.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idealize</ent>⟦br⟧
